#. (itstool) path: page/p
#: help/C/index.page:11
msgid "Truco is a popular card game played with a Spanish deck (or specific subset of French deck). The goal is to reach 12 points."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: section/title
#: help/C/index.page:14
msgid "How to Play"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: help/C/index.page:15
msgid "Each game consists of \"rounds\" (Mãos), worth 1 point by default. To win a round, a team must win 2 out of 3 \"tricks\" (Vazas)."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: item/p
#: help/C/index.page:18
msgid "<strong>Dealing:</strong> Each player receives 3 cards."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: item/p
#: help/C/index.page:19
msgid "<strong>Play:</strong> Players play one card per trick. The highest card wins."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: item/p
#: help/C/index.page:20
msgid "<strong>Ties:</strong> If the first trick is tied, the winner of the second trick wins the round. If the second is also tied, the winner of the third wins. If all 3 are tied, no points are awarded (or rules vary)."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: section/title
#: help/C/index.page:25
msgid "Calling Truco"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: help/C/index.page:26
msgid "At any player's turn, they can call \"Truco!\" to raise the stakes of the round."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: item/p
#: help/C/index.page:28
msgid "<strong>Truco</strong>: Raises value to 3 points."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: item/p
#: help/C/index.page:29
msgid "<strong>Seis (6)</strong>: Respondent can raise to 6."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: item/p
#: help/C/index.page:30
msgid "<strong>Nove (9)</strong>: Re-raise to 9."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: item/p
#: help/C/index.page:31
msgid "<strong>Doze (12)</strong>: Maximum value."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: help/C/index.page:33
msgid "If a team refuses a Truco challenge, they lose the current round, and the opposing team scores the points at the previous stake level."
msgstr ""

